Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
hello, little guy. so you want to go across a street. You must be very careful, especially wh you see lots of traffic. first, you need to find a place with a pavement marks. Then look your right, check if any cars are coming. Then look your left. if you do not see any cars coming from both directions, then you can enter the street. otherwise, have eye contact with the drivers. Enter street when they notice you.